I wake up on a cold, concrete floor. I sit up and look around. I'm back here. Is this punishment? Or a form of repentance? It doesn't matter anymore. I stand up and walk, passing by old shop fronts with signs rotting after years of neglect. [50% OFF SELECTED ITEMS!] Curiously, the damp smell of mold and pestilence is nowhere to be found. Only the sharp, metallic smell of blood hits my lungs. [LAST-DAY SALE, EVERYTHING MUST GO!] Where is he? [90% DISCOUNT ON THE TRUTH!] Why am I here? [FACE IT!] I think of this as I try to find what this place wants me to find. My mind stirs as I recall my dream. Maybe... Maybe I got off easy. Maybe this is my delayed limbo. I couldn't do anything for him, nor her. [YOGA CLASSES 35% OFF!] Reaching a crossroads, I turn left. It's easy to find my way through this derelict place, so alien yet so familiar. Eventually I see it again, and I face my truth.

