I used to have an uncle.

He was a great man.

Bang! Said the gun.

First shot tore through his hand.

Second pierced his chest.

Third, in the brain.

In all he did, he tried his best.

His end full of pain.





I forget what he looks like now, and that scares me.







Time passes by faster than you know.








Where did my youth go?















