|body=<div class="blurquote-noperson">{{Blurquote|image=Imissheralready.jpg|quote-text=...Do you ever wonder if you actually mean anything to anyone? Like, you could be having a conversation with them, laughing and smiling, but when you say goodbye and leave, do you think you still linger in their mind? Or are you forgotten like some detail in the background of their day? Do they remember you as much as they remember the color of their cashier's shoes at the supermarket? When will be the very last time your name leaves a person's lips, or your presence leaves their mind? I don't want to be forgotten, for nobody to know what my name means anymore. I'm scared of that more than anything else.
<br>...Will you forget me too, after this?|person=}}</div>}}

I weep for what I have lost and what I stand to lose. Rubbing the tears from my eyes, I notice a tiny white switch on the wall. Do log cabins have light switches? I have no idea. It seems compelling to flick it, like it was put there for me... Though, I don't mind leaving it off, too.

