<center><span style="font-family:Sekuya"><big><big><big><big><big><big>NO! YOU'RE RUINING ''EVERYTHING''!</big></big></big></big></big></big></span></center>











I clutch the documents in my hand. I grip them tightly. As tight as I can. I don't want to believe it. I refuse to believe it.  

<center><span style="font-family:Sekuya"><big><big><big><big><big><big>WHY COULDN'T YOU LEAVE IT BE?</big></big></big></big></big></big></span></center>

I... I had to know. This was what was best for me.

<center><span style="font-family:Sekuya"><big><big><big><big>I JUST WANTED TO SAVE YOU FROM THE PAIN. IF YOU HAD JUST PLAYED THE TAPE, YOU COULD HAVE BEEN FREE. YOU COULD HAVE FORGOTTEN.</big></big></big></big></span></center>


...Forget?

Why would I want to forget?

I am the sum of all I've done.

Nothing changes that.

For now, and forevermore.

I'm back at the car, and now I see it. Blood pools on the floor around it. My blood. 

But where is he?

<center><span style="font-family:Sekuya"><big><big><big><big><big><big>HE'S SAFE. HE SURVIVED.</big></big></big></big></big></big></span></center>

A knot in my chest looses, as well as my muscles. I feel my body start to fail me and I collapse to the floor. I cry. I cry and I cry.

I don't want to be forgotten.

<center><span style="font-family:Sekuya"><big><big><big><big><big><big>FORGETTING IS PART OF LIFE. YOU CANNOT BE REMEMBERED FOREVER.</big></big></big></big></big></big></span></center>

I understand now. As long as those I hold dear remember me until the life fades from them, as long as they tell my tale as best as they can, I I will be remembered. Not for long, but for long enough.

I smile as I feel my body shutting down. I close my eyes, for the very last time, surrounded by the most beautiful forest I have ever seen.

<span style="background:linear-gradient(to right, #FFFFFF,#130B2B); -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; -webkit-background-clip: text;">Goodbye.</span>
















